main event: An unidentified object was observed moving in a non-linear path, changing brilliance and direction, in Ocean City, Maryland on May 4, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 8 minutes and described the object as bright and star-like,The object was reportedly moving faster than a jet and produced no sound,The witness concluded it could possibly be a balloon despite its unusual motion,A prior report indicated that no object was visible in the area on May 1, 1963,The document was part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings.
witness description: A witness reported observing the object and completed a questionnaire for Project Blue Book.
